
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `bzip2` baraye feeshorde kardan (compress) file-ha estefade mishavad ta size-e anha koochak shavad. File-haye feeshorde shode ba پسوند `.bz2` negah dari mishavand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `bzip2 -k file`  --> 📦 File asli ra negah midarad va yek copy feeshorde shode misazad.
    🔹 `bzip2 -d file.bz2` --> 🔓 File feeshorde shode ra baz mikonad (decompress).
    🔹 `bzip2 -f file`  --> Force --> Agar file hamnam mojood bashad, override mikonad.
    🔹 `bzip2 -v file`  --> Verbose --> Etela'at bishtar dar morede feeshordegi namayesh midahad.
    🔹 `bzip2 -1 file`  --> 🚀  Feshordegi sari'tar ama ba size bozorgtar (az 1 ta 9, 1 sari'tarin).
    🔹 `bzip2 -9 file`  --> 🎯 Feshordegi bishtar ama ba sor'at kamtar (az 1 ta 9, 9 kamtarin).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ bzip2 myfile.txt

    🔹 File `myfile.txt` ra feeshorde mikonad va be `myfile.txt.bz2` tabdil mikonad va file asli ra hazf mikonad.

    $ bzip2 -k myfile.txt

    🔹 File `myfile.txt` ra feeshorde mikonad va be `myfile.txt.bz2` tabdil mikonad va file asli ra negah midarad.

    $ bzip2 -d myfile.txt.bz2

    🔹 File `myfile.txt.bz2` ra baz mikonad va be `myfile.txt` tabdil mikonad va file asli feeshorde shode ra hazf mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ bzip2 -v myfile.txt

    🔹 File `myfile.txt` ra feeshorde mikonad va etela'at marboote be amaliyat ra dar terminal namayesh midahad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `bzip2` command is used to compress files, reducing their size. Compressed files are stored with the `.bz2` extension.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `bzip2 -k file`  --> 📦 Keeps the original file and creates a compressed copy.
    🔹 `bzip2 -d file.bz2` --> 🔓 Decompresses a compressed file.
    🔹 `bzip2 -f file`  --> Force --> Overwrites existing files with the same name.
    🔹 `bzip2 -v file`  --> Verbose --> Shows more information about the compression process.
    🔹 `bzip2 -1 file`  --> 🚀 Faster compression but with a larger file size (from 1 to 9, 1 is fastest).
    🔹 `bzip2 -9 file`  --> 🎯 Higher compression but with slower speed (from 1 to 9, 9 is slowest).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ bzip2 myfile.txt

    🔹 Compresses the file `myfile.txt` to `myfile.txt.bz2` and removes the original file.

    $ bzip2 -k myfile.txt

    🔹 Compresses the file `myfile.txt` to `myfile.txt.bz2` and keeps the original file.

    $ bzip2 -d myfile.txt.bz2

    🔹 Decompresses the file `myfile.txt.bz2` to `myfile.txt` and removes the original compressed file.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ bzip2 -v myfile.txt

    🔹 Compresses the file `myfile.txt` and shows information about the process in the terminal.
